  "The upper limit changes randomly": "",
  "In an accumulation function F(x) = integral from a to x of f(t) dt, the upper limit x is a variable. This makes F a function of x: as x changes, the region of integration changes and so does the accumulated value.": "",
  "What is a 'dummy variable' in the context of accumulation functions?": "",
